{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52a6ff51-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1401"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1401"},"text":"§ 1401.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Stockholder’s derivative action","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any civil action by a stockholder on behalf of his corporation may be prosecuted in any judicial district where the corporation might have sued the same defendants.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52a6ff52-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/936"},"text":"62 Stat. 936","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52a6ff53-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52a6ff54-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 112 (part) (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s51"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 51","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1101"},"text":"36 Stat. 1101","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1922-09-19/ch345"},"text":"Sept. 19, 1922, ch. 345","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/849"},"text":"42 Stat. 849","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1925-03-04/ch526/s1"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1925, ch. 526, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/1264"},"text":"43 Stat. 1264","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1936-04-16/ch230"},"text":"Apr. 16, 1936, ch. 230","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/1213"},"text":"49 Stat. 1213","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For disposition of other provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s112"},"text":"section 112 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., see reviser’s note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1391"},"text":"section 1391 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “civil action” were substituted for “suit,” in view of Rule 2 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “other than said corporation,” after “same defendants,” were omitted as superfluous. Obviously a corporation would not be suing itself.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes were made in phraseology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
